  <title translate="true">How to start my motion at 30º not at 0º</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">FAQs<keyword translate="true">How to Edit Motion Start</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">How to start my motion at 30º not at 0º</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Frequently, a segment in your motion lies across the 0º timing mark. In this case you will want to move Blend-Point #1 from 0º. When you move Blend-Point #1, the whole motions moves by the same angle. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">To move the Blend-Point #1 to an angle that this not 0º, edit the </text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header" translate="true">Motion-Start</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> parameter in the </text><text styleclass="Element-Header" translate="true">Blend-Point Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#83;&#84;&#69;&#80;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo STEP" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo STEP"><text styleclass="HowTo STEP" translate="true">Open the Blend-Point Editor...</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:144px; height:62px;">
